OL,3,CNew cancer centre given the go ahead
OL,5,FAt the moment, cancer patients are
OL,6,Ftreated in a cramped unit in a
OL,7,Fbuilding that is no longer fit for
OL,8,Fpurpose.
OL,10,FBill Shay, who has skin cancer has
OL,11,Fregular visits to the cancer unit at
OL,12,Fthe Royal Sussex County Hospital in
OL,13,FBrighton. He says he can't fault his
OL,14,Fcare but, "there are sometimes not
OL,15,Fenough chairs in the chemo with these
OL,16,Fbig comfy chairs, the easy chairs to
OL,17,Fhave the infusions."
OL,19,FThe roof in the current building is
OL,20,Fleaking which can damage equipment and
OL,21,Fsometimes delay care and treatment.
